  "elapsed_s": 8.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 50,
      "text": "So while he was out of the room, I opened the window and jumped out and left.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 51,
      "text": "Eventually, I made my way with-- in a Belgian repatriation train, without a visa.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 52,
      "text": "And I jumped off the train in the first Belgian city that we arrived at, through the window and-- and then took the next train to Brussels and-- and from there to Antwerp.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 53,
      "text": "And it was a very complicated business of how, in one day, I had to obtain all sorts of documentation, in order to get on the boat.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 54,
      "text": "And then when I finally got on the boat-- and I was one of seven civilians on-- on the boat-- you have to understand that most of Europe was still in-- in shambles and-- and disarray.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 55,
      "text": "And there was no civilian transatlantic transport yet or any communication.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 56,
      "text": "What I had to go through to get the first telephone call to-- to my father was a-- is an unbelievable and-- and complicated story.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 57,
      "text": "But eventually, I-- I got on-- on this Liberty ship, which carried 40 American soldiers and several hundred SS dogs that were being brought as stock to-- to the United States, I presume for police purposes.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 58,
      "text": "And we had to ship in at about 3 o'clock in the afternoon or sometime like that, at about 7 o'clock.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 59,
      "text": "And this was in a-- what was a military port in Antwerp.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 60,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] [INAUDIBLE] An American officer appeared, and the seven civilians had to come down the gangplank.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 61,
      "text": "And he was examining [? the ?] papers.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 62,
      "text": "And he takes a look at my passport, and he says, oh, enemy alien.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 63,
      "text": "Of course I was-- I had a Hungarian passport, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] which I obtained through another very adventurous story.",
      "word_count": 21
    }
  ],
